title: In New Jersey, Redistricting Helped Most Incumbents Win Big
description: Often a swing state, New Jersey is now divided into congressional districts that are even more purely red or blue than before.
dc:creator: Tracey Tully

media:content.media:credit: Andrew Seng for The New York Times
media:content.media:description: Tom Kean Jr., a Republican, addressed supporters on election night. On Wednesday morning, the incumbent, Rep. Tom Malinowski, conceded to Mr. Kean.
